<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She's currently in the midst of planning her wedding with fiancé Bradley Dack, after months of putting it on the back burner amid the first COVID-19 lockdown.</p>

<p>And Olivia Attwood, 29, looked as loved up as ever on Tuesday, when she was spotted stepping out for a romantic meal with her 26-year-old partner in Manchester.</p>

<p>The former Love Island star arrived Asha's Indian restaurant arm-in-arm with her beau after a day of shooting scenes for her new show, Olivia Meets Her Match.</p>

<p>Fine dining: Olivia Attwood looked as loved up as ever on Tuesday, when she was spotted stepping out for a romantic meal with her fiancé in Manchester</p>

<p>Olivia looked casually cool for the outing, donning a black crop top and leggings with a baggy plaid blue shirt.</p>

<p>Donning a pair of Dior high-top sneakers, the blonde beauty rounded out her ensemble with a cobalt blue Chanel leather handbag.</p>

<p>Wearing her golden locks in long shoulder-length waves with a centre-parting, the TOWIE star glammed up her look with a dewy palette of makeup. </p>

<p>Production: Earlier in the day, a cameraman was seen trailing the pair as they strolled through the city's streets to shoot scenes for her new show, Olivia Meets Her Match</p>

<p>For his part, footballer Bradley teamed black skinny jeans with a patterned top and a jacket as he enjoyed his day out with his wife-to-be.</p>

<p>Earlier in the day, a cameraman was seen trailing the pair as they strolled through the city's streets to shoot scenes for Olivia's new show. </p>

<p>Last week, Olivia appeared to be in full wedding planning mode, as she was seen trying on a selection of gowns at Blackburn Bridal Couture. </p>

<p>Joined by her mother Jenny for the day, the media personality seemed to be in her element as she slipped in and out of gowns. </p>

<p>Casually cool: TV personality Olivia looked casually cool for the outing, donning a black crop top and leggings with a baggy plaid blue shirt</p>

<p>Olivia looked sensational in a slinky column gown with sheer panels and lace adornment.</p>

<p>The bride-to-be was a vision in the dress, which featured a low cut neckline and sheer full length skirt with a mini train. </p>

<p>Sharing a quick video inside the boutique, Olivia mused: 'I've started looking for my dress today. My crew are in tow... because why not? Let's get married baby!'</p>

<p>During the exciting outing Olivia was seen eyeing up a number of possible gowns and searching through racks to find the right one. </p>

<p>Fans will be able to see more gowns when her new reality TV show airs on ITVBe this autumn.</p>

<p>Ensemble: For his part, footballer Bradley teamed black skinny jeans with a patterned top and a jacket as he enjoyed his day out with his wife-to-be</p>

<p>The eight-episode series will follow Olivia and her Blackburn Rovers footballer fiancé Bradley as they plan their wedding and buy their first home in Cheshire.</p>

<p>The couple got engaged in Dubai last year and the programme will document their relationship as they prepare to take it the next level, with Olivia planning her dream wedding.</p>

<p>Olivia previously had her own reality show with ex-boyfriend Chris Hughes called Crackin' On.</p>

<p>However, their relationship took a turn for the worse when Chris, 27, broke up with her on camera, telling her the relationship wasn't making him happy anymore. </p>

<p>Bride-to-be: Last week, Olivia revealed she was back in planning mode as she tried on wedding dresses at Blackburn Bridal Couture</p>

<p>Bride squad: Olivia had her mother Jenny with her to help pick out a gown, who she cheekily referred to as 'queen of the hoes' </p>

<p>Olivia then reunited with Bradley, whom she was with before Love Island, while Chris found love with his now ex-girlfriend Jesy Nelson.</p>

<p>Speaking to OK! magazine earlier this month, Olivia revealed that her wedding plans were thrown up in the air when the coronavirus pandemic hit. </p>

<p>She explained: 'We had our hearts set on a destination wedding, but I’m opening up to the idea of a UK wedding because we want to get married next year and definitely can’t afford to go into quarantine for two weeks.</p>

<p>'I’m going to look at some UK venues and see if they can turn my head.' </p>

<p>Cute couple: Olivia's new eight-episode series will follow Olivia and her Blackburn Rovers footballer fiancé Bradley, 26, as they plan their wedding and buy their first home in Cheshire</p>
